(198, 1, '2022-07-06 12:41:02', '2022-07-06 12:41:02', '<!-- wp:html -->\n<p class=\"inside-page-content__main--description\">\n          Sanskrithi School of Engineering has entered into Memoranda of\n          Understanding with many corporate and industrial organizations to\n          strengthen the skill sets it provides its students. Ranging from\n          educational material to soft skills that improve the employability of\n          the students, these MOUs will help SSE (to) create character-shaping\n          and life changing training modules for students, helping them garner\n          more success in life – as employees and as human beings.\n        </p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">RISE, Austria</h2>\n        <p>\n          This Memorandum of Understanding (“MOU”) outlines the intentions of\n          RISE, VIENNA, Austria, and Sanskrithi School of Engineering regarding\n          the establishment of a long–term cooperative endeavor intended to\n          create mutually advantageous relationships in academics.\n        </p>\n        <h3 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h3\">Focus of the MOU</h3>\n        <ul class=\"inside-page-content__main--ul\">\n          <li>\n            RISE will support to establish an R & D lab in SSE and maintained by\n            SSE within the prescribed framework.\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            RISE and SSE facilitate the students under exchange program where\n            SSE students get an opportunity to visit Vienna for technology\n            exchange\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            RISE will depute two faculties to SSE on a regular basis to teach\n            various engineering subjects and Value-added courses\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            RISE and SSE work together to make SSE an integral part of RISE in\n            the long run.\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            RISE and SSE work together to organize international conference,\n            FDPs, Hackathons etc.\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">IAESTE, India</h2>\n        <p>\n          This Memorandum of Association (MOA) is made between IAESTE-India and\n          Sanskrithi Group of Institutions, Sanskrithi School of Engineering\n        </p>\n        <ul class=\"inside-page-content__main--ul\">\n          <li>\n            To associate with IAESTE-India through the student exchange program\n            of IAESTE by providing internships to foreign students.\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            Promoting international understanding through exchanging of students\n            worldwide\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">APSSDC</h2>\n        <p>\n          APSSDC is a unique organization formed as a public private partnership\n          (PPP) corporation to promote skill-development & entrepreneurship in\n          the state of Andhra Pradesh. Our MOU with them will allow us to give\n          our students an opportunity to learn the career skills that will help\n          them succeed.\n        </p>\n        <h3 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h3\">Focus of the MOU</h3>\n        <ul class=\"inside-page-content__main--ul\">\n          <li>\n            To make qualitative improvements in imparting technical skills by\n            setting up- CM skill Excellence Centre\n          </li>\n          <li>To promote industries</li>\n          <li>Train student to improve employability</li>\n          <li>\n            Promote Research and Development and innovation for existing\n            industries\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">AIC-SKU</h2>\n        <p>\n          AIC-SKU Confederation is an Atal Incubation Centre (AIC) at Sri\n          Krishnadevaraya University (SKU) supported by the Atal Innovation\n          Mission, NITI Aayog, Govt. of India and AP Innovation Society, Govt.\n          of Andhra Pradesh. This collaboration will create and inculcate\n          entrepreneurial spirit in the student community, grooming start-ups\n          ideas and emerging businesses in the sectors which lead to job\n          creation.\n        </p>\n        <h3 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h3\">Focus of the MOU</h3>\n        <ul class=\"inside-page-content__main--ul\">\n          <li>\n            To carry out activities and events that develop a start-up ecosystem\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            To create an entrepreneurship ecosystem in the SSE campus that\n            motivate students to think out of box innovations.\n          </li>\n          <li>To empower the faculty with the entrepreneurial spirit</li>\n          <li>To create new IP asset</li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">\n          SKYFI LABS PVT LTD, BANGALORE\n        </h2>\n        <p>\n          This Memorandum of Association (MOA) is made between Sanskrithi School\n          of Engineering, and Skyfi Education Labs Pvt. Ltd, Bangalore.\n        </p>\n        <h3 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h3\">Focus of the MOU</h3>\n        <ul class=\"inside-page-content__main--ul\">\n          <li>Provide a quality workshop according to the structure manne</li>\n          <li>\n            Provide “Certificate of Appreciation” to the student volunteers\n            assisting in organizing the event\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            Provide “Certificate of Completion” to all the students who\n            successfully complete the workshop\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">VAJRASOFT INC, USA</h2>\n        <p>\n          The purpose of this Memorandum of Understanding (the “MOU”) is to\n          build strategic alliance between Sanskrithi School of Engineering and\n          VajraSoft Inc. VajraSoft Inc shall be Innovation Partner to help\n          Sanskrithi – its proposed Hardware Accelerator and Startup accelerator\n          focused on IoT, Healthcare, AgTech, Robotics, Artificial\n          Intelligence,MachineLearningandDeepLearninginnovationsTechnology\n          innovations from Lab to Market, offer training course offerings and\n          also provide Technology Intelligence for making right R&D investments\n          and accelerating R&D innovations and other purposes mutually agreed\n          upon.\n        </p>\n        <h3 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h3\">Focus of the MOU</h3>\n        <ul class=\"inside-page-content__main--ul\">\n          <li>\n            Provide access to the facilities, early-stage startups, nurtured as\n            part of Sanskrithi initiative\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            Provision access to startup ideas for idea capture, ideation, and\n            Innovation capacity building\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">EDUSKILLS</h2>\n        <p>\n          SSE has tied up with Eduskills, a foundation that offers digital\n          content and courses of up to five global academy programs, creating\n          LMS (learning management systems) for SSE’s programs, as and where\n          possible.\n        </p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">QUANTUM LEARNING</h2>\n        <p>\n          This Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) is made between Sanskrithi\n          School of Engineering, and Quantum Learning ,A Microsoft GTP (Global\n          Training Partner & Certiport CATC, NewDelhi. Quantum Learning offers\n          programs bundled with certifications of MICROSOFT,APPLE,EC\n          COUNCEIL,AUTODESK,ADOBE,MISSISSIPPI STATE UNIVERSITY,UNIVERSITY OF\n          TEXAS to SSE students.\n        </p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">BLACKBUCK ACADEMY</h2>\n        <p>\n          This Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) is made between Sanskrithi\n          School of Engineering and Blackbuck Engineers Pvt Ltd, Hyderabad ,\n          delivers Advanced Skills in Emerging Technologies and provide industry\n          focus to the students. Blackbuck offers certifications trainings and\n          FDPs in\n        </p>\n        <ul class=\"inside-page-content__main--ul\">\n          <li>Artificial Intelligence</li>\n          <li>Machine Leaning</li>\n          <li>Data Sciences</li>\n          <li>Cloud</li>\n          <li>Cyber Security</li>\n          <li>IoT</li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">TSILICON</h2>\n        <p>\n          This Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) is made between Sanskrithi\n          School of Engineering, and TSILICON, Bengaluru, with the objective of\n          encouraging research and innovation in the domain of VSLI and AI/ML.\n        </p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">CISCO-ACADEMY</h2>\n        <p>\n          This collaboration between Sanskrithi School of Engineering and CISCO\n          Academy heps to prepare students for career opportunities in ICT ,\n          continuing education, and globally recognized certification with the\n          following courses:\n        </p>\n        <ul class=\"inside-page-content__main--ul\">\n          <li>IT Essentials</li>\n          <li>CCNA Routing and Switching</li>\n          <li>CCNA Security</li>\n          <li>CCNP</li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">MICROCHIP ACADEMIC</h2>\n        <p>\n          SSE and the Microchip Academic program offer unique world-class\n          technical programs in networking, cybersecurity, cloud computing,\n          automation, RPA and other industry 4.0 skills to our institution and\n          our students, expanding their digital skills.\n        </p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">\n          PALO ALTO CYBERSECURITY ACADEMY\n        </h2>\n        <p>\n          We have tied up with the Palo Alto Cybersecurity Academy to help our\n          students prepare for cybersecurity careers. They will learn\n          cybersecurity fundamentals, network security, cloud security and how a\n          security operations centre (SOC) works via the hands-on curriculum.\n        </p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">RED HAT ACADEMY</h2>\n        <p>\n          With the Red Hat Academy,SSE intends to provide students training from\n          the recognized leader of Linux in the IT industry through flexible\n          courses designed for Linux, cloud, and development technologies.\n        </p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">AWS</h2>\n        <p>\n          As cloud technologies continue to help organizations transform at a\n          rapid pace, employees with the necessary cloud skills are in high\n          demand. AWS Academy provides a ready-to-teach cloud computing\n          curriculum that prepares students to pursue industry-recognized\n          certifications and in-demand cloud jobs.\n        </p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"inside-page-content__main--h2\">\n          BLUEPRISM UNIVERSITY ACADEMY\n        </h2>\n        <p>\n          This joint effort between SSE and the Blueprism University Academy\n          makes available customized, role-based, public, and private training\n          to students and faculty , giving them an opportunity to enhance their\n          knowledge, network with the best and brightest, and help them become\n          key players in shaping the future of intelligent automation.\n        </p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->', 'Affiliation and Recognition', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'affiliation-and-recognition', '', '', '2022-07-06 12:43:47', '2022-07-06 12:43:47', '', 60, 'http://localhost/?page_id=198', 7, 'page', '', 0),
